Eutelsat Communications and MultiChoice Africa have signed a nine-year contract for expansion of DSTV platform.In a statement released at the IBC 2016 exhibition in Amsterdam, Eutelsat said the new contract for one transponder a wireless communications, monitoring, or control device that picks up and automatically responds to an incoming signal will further enhance digital video entertainment services in Africa.MultiChoice Africa CEO Tim Jacobs said the additional capacity will enable the pay-TV firm improve customer experience. Eutelsat s chief commercial officer Michel Azibert said the contract anchors its cluster of high-power satellites.